<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7376&amp;p=72708#p72708"><![CDATA[
Since 2 ^ 14 = 16384, for the CHR you only need 14 address lines, so A14 and up should be grounded. For the PRG, 2 ^16 = 65536, so A16 and up must be grounded. I believe /WE must be connected to +5V.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Thu Jan 13, 2011 2:30 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
