<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7376&amp;p=72696#p72696"><![CDATA[
If you don't double-up the PRG and CHR before you flash it to a larger chip, you'll need to ground any unused address lines. For example, if the result after split was 64 KiB, you'll need to ground A16 on up.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Jan 13, 2011 9:16 am</p><hr />
