<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7376&amp;p=72690#p72690"><![CDATA[
I don't recall if there was a reason tat SMB2(J) is MMC3 and not CNROM and likewise, I'm not sure why I'm replying to this... Senseless generosity I guess...<br /><br />49F040 ..........MMC3 Mapper Pin #<br />pin 1 (A18)--- 23<br />pin 2 (A16)--- 21<br />pin30 (A17)--- 25<br />(/CE)-----------26<br />(GND)----------28<br /><br />If SMB3 uses the mask ROMs that I remember it using, the DIP pinout would be:<br /><br />49F040 ..........512K DIP Pin #<br />pin 1 (A18)--- 2<br />pin 2 (A16)--- 24<br />pin30 (A17)--- 1<br />(/CE)-----------22<br />(GND)---------16<br /><br />Alternatively:<br /><br />49F040 ..........256K DIP Pin #<br />pin 1 (A18)--- NC<br />pin 2 (A16)--- 24<br />pin30 (A17)--- 1<br />(/CE)-----------22<br />(GND)---------16<br /><br />You should read the Wiki and other data pages for more info... This is all documented here. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_cool.gif" alt="8)" title="Cool" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4070">Xious</a> — Thu Jan 13, 2011 6:17 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
